Step 1: Deploy RDS Infrastructure on VMware

Create VMs: RDWeb Server | RD Gateway | Connection Broker |Session Host

Install Roles:
Server Manager
 → Add Roles
 → Remote Desktop Services
 Verify: http://servername/RDWeb
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Step 2: Configure SSL Certificate

Generate Certificate: Internal CA

Bind Certificate: RDWeb | RD Gateway | RD Broker

Verify: https://rdweb.company.com/RDWeb
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 3: Configure Azure Entra ID

Prerequisites: Azure Entra P1/P2 | Global Administrator | Hybrid Identity

Navigate: Entra Portal → Applications → Enterprise Applications → Application Proxy

Enable: Application Proxy
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 4: Install Application Proxy Connector

Provision VM: Windows Server | Domain Joined

Recommended: 2 CPU or 4 GB RAM

Download Connector:
Navigate: Entra Portal → Application Proxy → Download Connector

Install: AADApplicationProxyConnectorInstaller.exe

Login: Global Admin Account

Verify Status: Active → Ready
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 5: Publish RDWeb

Navigate: Enterprise Applications → New Application → On-Premises Application

Configure:
Internal URL: https://rdweb.company.local/RDWeb
External URL: https://rdweb-contoso.msappproxy.net

Connector Group: Default Connector Group

Protocol: HTTPS
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 6: Enable Pre-Authentication

Select: Azure Entra ID

Enable: Conditional Access

Flow:

User
 ↓
Entra Authentication
 ↓
Application Proxy
 ↓
RDWeb
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 7: Configure MFA

Navigate: Entra ID → Conditional Access

Create Policy:
Target:
RDWeb Application
Grant:
Require MFA
Conditions: Outside Corporate Network | High Risk Login | privileged Users

Flow:
Username
 ↓
Password
 ↓
MFA
 ↓
RDWeb Access
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 8: Publish RD Gateway

Publish: RD Gateway

Internal URL: https://rdgateway.company.local

External URL: https://rdgateway.msappproxy.net

Configure: HTTP Passthrough

Required for: RDP Traffic | Remote Desktop Connectivity
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 10: Test End User Access

Access: https://rdweb-contoso.msappproxy.net/RDWeb

Process:
Login
 ↓
MFA
 ↓
RDWeb Portal
 ↓
Launch RemoteApp
 ↓
RD Gateway
 ↓
Session Host
